The paper discusses multiuser diversity in cognitive radio networks, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), cognitive radio (cs.CR), multimedia (cs.MM), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on the technical aspects of multiuser diversity in cognitive radio networks, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories.
